results.name: Expansion of 1/(1-x^5-x^6).
comment: Number of compositions of n into parts 5 and 6. [_Joerg Arndt_, Jun 27 2013]
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000 (terms 0..1000 from Vincenzo Librandi)
Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients, signature (0,0,0,0,1,1).
formula: a(n) = a(n-6) + a(n-5). - _Jon E. Schoenfield_, Aug 07 2006
program: (MAGMA) m:=70; R<x>:=PowerSeriesRing(Integers(), m); Coefficients(R!(1/(1-x^5-x^6))); /* or */ I:=[1,0,0,0,0,1]; [n le 6 select I[n] else Self(n-5)+Self(n-6): n in [1..70]]; // _Vincenzo Librandi_, Jun 27 2013
